an> Room</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">בַּיִת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(bayith)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:11\">1CH 28:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:11\">1CH 28:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:17\">EZK 41:17</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">גַּב</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(gev)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:24\">EZK 16:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:31\">EZK 16:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:39\">EZK 16:39</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">חֶדֶר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(cheder)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:30\">GEN 43:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:25\">DEU 32:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:1\">JDG 15:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:9\">JDG 16:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:12\">JDG 16:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:10\">2SA 13:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:10\">2SA 13:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:15\">1KI 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:30\">PSA 105:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:27\">PRO 7:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:4\">PRO 24:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:4\">SNG 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song3:4\">SNG 3:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:20\">ISA 26:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:12\">EZK 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:16\">JOL 2:16</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">יָצוּעַ, יָצִיעַ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(yatsu‘a, yatsi‘a)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:6\">1KI 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:6\">1KI 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:10\">1KI 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:10\">1KI 6:10</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">לִשְׁכָּה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(lishkah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:22\">1SA 9:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:11\">2KI 23:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:26\">1CH 9:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:33\">1CH 9:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:28\">1CH 23:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:12\">1CH 28:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:11\">2CH 31:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:29\">EZR 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:6\">EZR 10:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:38\">NEH 10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:39\">NEH 10:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:40\">NEH 10:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:4\">NEH 13:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:5\">NEH 13:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:8\">NEH 13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:9\">NEH 13:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:2\">JER 35:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:4\">JER 35:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:4\">JER 35:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:4\">JER 35:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer36:10\">JER 36:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer36:12\">JER 36:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer36:20\">JER 36:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer36:21\">JER 36:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:17\">EZK 40:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:17\">EZK 40:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:38\">EZK 40:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:44\">EZK 40:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:45\">EZK 40:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:46\">EZK 40:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:10\">EZK 41:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:1\">EZK 42:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:4\">EZK 42:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:5\">EZK 42:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:7\">EZK 42:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:7\">EZK 42:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:8\">EZK 42:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:9\">EZK 42:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:9\">EZK 42:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:10\">EZK 42:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:11\">EZK 42:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:12\">EZK 42:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:13\">EZK 42:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:13\">EZK 42:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:13\">EZK 42:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:19\">EZK 44:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:5\">EZK 45:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:19\">EZK 46:19</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">נִשְׁכָּה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(nishkah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:30\">NEH 3:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:44\">NEH 12:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:7\">NEH 13:7</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">צֵלָע</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(tsela‘)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:5\">1KI 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:8\">1KI 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:3\">1KI 7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:9\">EZK 41:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:9\">EZK 41:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:11\">EZK 41:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:26\">EZK 41:26</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">θάλαμος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(thalamos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc1:18\">3MA 1:18</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">παστοφόριον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pastoforion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc4:38\">1MA 4:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc4:57\">1MA 4:57</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd8:58\">1ES 8:58</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd9:1\">1ES 9:1</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The room was a subdivision in a house or other structure.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The meaning of the Hebrew word <em>gev</em> in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:24\">EZK 16:24</a> is uncertain. While <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> renders it “vaulted chamber,” most translations prefer a word or phrase that indicates a place of forbidden worship, for example, “shrine[s]” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New King James Version (1982)\">NKJV</abbr>, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr>, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New American Standard Bible\">NASB</abbr>), “place to worship gods” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr>), or “mound” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr>).</p>\n<p>The Hebrew word <em>tsela‘</em> appears first in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:22\">GEN 2:22</a> as a rib of Adam. Certain rooms in Solomon’s Temple and in the ideal Temple described by Ezekiel ran along the sides of the Temple, and perhaps from some resemblance to the human rib cage they are also designated as <em>tsela‘</em>. See the discussion of <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:5\">1KI 6:5</a> in <em>A Handbook on 1–2 Kings</em>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
